# MoneyMatrix

MoneyMatrix is a personal finance management application that helps users track their expenses and incomes, analyze spending patterns, and manage money flow efficiently.

---

## Table of Contents
- [Features](#features)
- [Tech Stack](#tech-stack)
- [Setup & Installation](#setup--installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [API Documentation](#api-documentation)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

---

## Features
- Add, update, and delete expenses and incomes.
- View transactions by category and date range.
- Analyze total spending per category.
- Aggregated monthly summaries for last 3 months.
- Secure authentication with JWT and Spring Security.
- Pagination for transaction listing.

---

## Tech Stack
- *Backend:* Java, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA
- *Database:* MySQL
- *Mapping:* MapStruct
- *Build Tool:* Maven
- *Testing:* JUnit, Mockito
- *Documentation:* Springdoc OpenAPI (Swagger)

---

## Setup & Installation

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Aakash-fstackdev/MoneyMatrix.git
cd MoneyMatrix  


spring:
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/moneymatrix
    username: root
    password: <your-password>


mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run


#Api Documentation
http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
